1e:["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Yes (Gong IQ v7.0; industry-leading transcription accuracy at 99.2%; multi-language speaker diarization + competitive mention tracking)"}]
1f:["$","tr","2",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**Email/SMS/Call Sequencing**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"✅ Native (up to 50-step sequences; A/B test variants; dynamic pause rules based on reply sentiment)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"✅ Native (Smart Sequences with behavioral triggers; integrates with RingCentral, Zoom Phone, Dialpad)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"❌ Requires Gong Connectors + third-party SEP (e.g., HubSpot Sales Hub or Apollo)"}]]}]
20:["$","tr","3",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**CRM Sync Depth**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Bi-directional sync with Salesforce (objects: Account, Contact, Lead, Opportunity, Task, Activity); supports custom objects & field-level mapping"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Bi-directional sync with Salesforce (full object support + CPQ & Service Cloud integration); native Microsoft Dynamics 365 sync"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Bi-directional sync with Salesforce (Lead/Opportunity only); limited custom object support; requires Gong for Salesforce Admin add-on ($49/user/mo)"}]]}]
21:["$","tr","4",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**AI Coaching & Playbooks**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in Coach AI with role-play simulations, skill scoring (e.g., “Discovery Question Depth”), and auto-suggested follow-ups"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"SalesLoft Coach AI delivers personalized micro-learning paths + live call nudges (“Ask about budget now”)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Gong Coach (included) offers conversation scorecards, skill gap analysis, and peer benchmarking — but *no sequencing or outreach automation*"}]]}]
22:["$","tr","5",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**Pricing (Annual, Billed Annually)**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Starter: $125/user/mo (min. 10 users) • Pro: $225/user/mo • Enterprise: Custom (starts at $325/user/mo; includes AI Governance Dashboard & SOC 2 Type II audit reports)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Engage: $150/user/mo (min. 15 users) • Growth: $245/user/mo • Scale: $345/user/mo (includes predictive lead scoring + RevOps dashboard)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Core: $149/user/mo (min. 20 users) • Advanced: $279/user/mo (includes Gong AI Search, Competitive Intelligence, Forecast Signals) • Enterprise: $415/user/mo (includes custom ML models + API sandbox)"}]]}]
23:["$","tr","6",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**Deployment Time (Avg.)**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"12–18 days (with certified partner)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"14–21 days (requires RevOps alignment for CPQ/Dynamics)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"7–10 days (lightest footprint; primarily ingestion + permissions)"}]]}]
24:["$","tr","7",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**Top Use Case in 2026**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Mid-market SaaS scaling outbound from 5 → 50 reps; needs full-stack sequencing + AI coaching + pipeline visibility"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Large enterprises (1,000+ reps) with complex CPQ, multi-product lines, and global compliance requirements"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Revenue teams prioritizing win/loss analysis, executive forecasting accuracy, and coaching at scale — *not* frontline execution"}]]}]
25:["$","tr","8",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"**G2 Score (Spring 2026)**"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"4.4/5 (1,284 reviews; praised for reliability & email deliverability)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"4.3/5 (942 reviews; strongest in “Ease of Admin” and “Reporting”)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"4.6/5 (2,107 reviews; #1 in “Value for Money” and “Conversation Insights”)"}]]}]
26:["$","h2","22",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Deep-Dive Platform Analysis"}]
27:["$","h3","24",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"**Outreach: The All-in-One Execution Engine**"}]
28:["$","p","25",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Outreach remains the most balanced SEP for teams that need *automation + intelligence + coaching* in one native stack. Its 2026 flagship feature — ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Outreach IQ Predictive Pause"}]," — halts sequences automatically when Gong-like signals (e.g., declining reply velocity, negative sentiment spikes) indicate disengagement, reducing spam complaints by 37% (per Outreach’s Q1 2026 Trust Report). Pros: best-in-class deliverability infrastructure (98.4% inbox placement rate), intuitive sequence builder, and robust API ecosystem (220+ native integrations). Cons: limited native conversational analytics depth vs. Gong; AI governance controls require Enterprise tier; Salesforce custom object sync adds $18K/year."]}]
29:["$","h3","27",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"**SalesLoft: The Enterprise Orchestrator**"}]
2a:["$","p","28",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["SalesLoft shines where process rigor meets scale. Its ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Revenue Orchestration Layer (ROL)"}]," — launched in late 2025 — unifies engagement data across SalesLoft, CPQ, Service Cloud, and marketing automation, feeding a single source of truth for RevOps dashboards. It’s the only platform offering out-of-the-box ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"compliance playbooks"}]," for HIPAA, FINRA, and APAC data residency. Pros: unmatched admin control, granular permissioning, and embedded predictive scoring (e.g., “Deal Health Score” combining engagement + CRM + intent data). Cons: steeper learning curve; mobile app lags in feature parity; starter tier lacks AI coaching."]}]
2b:["$","h3","30",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"**Gong: The Revenue Truth Engine**"}]
2c:["$","p","31",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Gong doesn’t *do* outreach — it *measures and improves* it. With 92% of Fortune 500 sales orgs using Gong for forecast accuracy (up from 68% in 2023), its strength lies in transforming conversations into actionable insights. The 2026 ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Competitive Signal Engine"}]," detects 147 vendor mentions across 22 languages and correlates them with win rates (e.g., “Teams mentioning ‘Snowflake’ 3+ times in discovery calls close 22% faster”). Pros: unrivaled transcription fidelity, powerful search (“Show me all calls where we missed budget questions”), and seamless executive reporting. Cons: zero native sequencing or cadence management; requires significant change management for rep adoption; expensive for small teams (<20 users)."]}]
2d:["$","h2","33",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"How to Choose Based on Team Size & Budget"}]
2e:["$","p","35",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"< 15 Reps / <$250K Annual RevOps Budget"}],": ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Outreach Starter"}]," is optimal. You get full sequencing, basic AI coaching, and reliable Salesforce sync without overpaying for unused enterprise features. Avoid Gong — its minimum 20-user license creates 33% overspend."]}]
2f:["$","p","36",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"15–75 Reps / $250K–$750K Budget"}],": ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"SalesLoft Growth"}]," or ",["$","strong","5",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Outreach Pro"}],", depending on priority. Choose SalesLoft if you run complex CPQ deals or need global compliance. Choose Outreach if speed-to-value and email/SMS execution are critical."]}]
30:["$","p","37",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"75+ Reps / $750K+ Budget"}],": ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Gong Advanced + SalesLoft Scale"}]," (or Outreach Enterprise) as a *complementary pair*. Leading teams (e.g., Datadog, Twilio) use Gong for coaching/forecasting and SalesLoft for execution — integrated via native bi-directional webhooks. Gong alone won’t move the needle on outbound volume."]}]
31:["$","h2","39",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"FAQ"}]
32:["$","p","41",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Q1: Does Outreach or SalesLoft offer built-in call recording?"}],""]}]
33:["$","p","42",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Neither does natively in 2026. Both require integration with cloud telephony providers (e.g., Zoom Phone, RingCentral, or Dialpad) for recording. Gong records directly via browser extension, desktop app, or native dialer — no telephony dependency."]}]
34:["$","p","44",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Q2: Can I use Gong with HubSpot instead of Salesforce?"}],""]}]
35:["$","p","45",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Yes — Gong supports HubSpot CRM (full bi-directional sync), Pipedrive, and Zoho CRM as of March 2026. However, Salesforce remains its most deeply integrated and audited connector."]}]
36:["$","p","47",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Q3: Is AI coaching in Outreach/SalesLoft truly automated, or does it require manual review?"}],""]}]
37:["$","p","48",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Fully automated in both. Outreach IQ and SalesLoft Coach AI generate real-time feedback, skill scores, and suggested next steps without human review — though managers can override or annotate insights."]}]
38:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Q4: Do any of these platforms support offline mode or mobile-first workflows?"}],""]}]
39:["$","p","51",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: SalesLoft leads here — its iOS/Android apps support full sequence management, call logging, and offline note-taking synced on reconnection. Outreach mobile is strong for notifications and quick replies; Gong mobile excels for listening and tagging calls on-the-go."]}]
3a:["$","p","53",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Q5: What’s the average ROI timeline per platform?"}],""]}]
3b:["$","p","54",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["A: Outreach: 3.2 months (driven by faster ramp time & higher reply rates). SalesLoft: 4.8 months (longer due to process alignment). Gong: 5.5 months (ROI manifests in forecast accuracy lift and reduced deal slippage — measurable after ~2 quarters of full adoption)."]}]
3c:["$","h2","56",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Final Recommendation"}]
3d:["$","p","58",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["There is no universal “winner.” **Outreach wins for growth-stage SaaS teams needing execution velocity and AI-powered coaching in one platform. SalesLoft wins for large, regulated enterprises requiring orchestration across complex systems and strict compliance. Gong wins for revenue leaders who prioritize *truth, not volume* — especially when forecasting, coaching quality, or competitive insight is the top KPI.** In 2026, the smartest buyers don’t choose one — they architect a stack: Gong for insight, Outreach or SalesLoft for action, and a modern CRM as the anchor. Your first step? Audit your *biggest revenue leak*: Is it poor outreach execution (→ Outreach), fragmented processes (→ SalesLoft), or blind spots in deal health (→ Gong)? Then build outward — not inward."]}]
